    "summary": "追溯冰淇淋、番茄和马铃薯的传播，理解食物跨文化流动。"
  },
  "sentences": [
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s1",
      "text": "The history of foods is never simple.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "食物的历史从来都不简单。",
      "g": "主系表结构",
      "d": "never 是频度副词，修饰系动词 is。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/gKvkLrTFipMairdLMuzgpP.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s2",
      "text": "Think of ice cream.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "想想冰淇淋。",
      "g": "祈使句",
      "d": "think of 意为“考虑，想起”。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/ZNzWQg48sHXbEfEawMpzJS.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s3",
      "text": "Many people see it as a Western dessert.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "许多人把它看作是一种西方甜点。",
      "g": "主谓宾宾补",
      "d": "see...as... 把...看作...。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/7yCLxGMgyYaGSZKtF8JGsj.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s4",
      "text": "However, this sweet treat actually came from China!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "然而，这种甜点实际上来自中国！",
      "g": "主谓状",
      "d": "come from 来自；actually 是副词修饰动词。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/6mbcvR2amVgEor3xBWkWoU.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s5",
      "text": "In the Zhou Dynasty, Chinese people began to store winter ice to enjoy in summer.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "在周朝，中国人开始储存冬天的冰，以便在夏天享用。",
      "g": "时间状语 + 主谓宾 + 目的状语",
      "d": "to enjoy... 是动词不定式作目的状语。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/4DYkRGyXJBQU2fzGGvFmgW.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s6",
      "text": "In the Song Dynasty, people started to make binglao – it just means “ice cream” in English.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "在宋朝，人们开始制作“冰酪”——在英语中它的意思就是“冰淇淋”。",
      "g": "并列句/解释说明",
      "d": "means 是谓语动词，意为“意思是”。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/NEkphfvYWjfGwAXfD7WSaR.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s7",
      "text": "It was a lot like modern ice cream.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "它很像现代的冰淇淋。",
      "g": "主系表",
      "d": "be like 像...；a lot 修饰 like 表示程度。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/jRVVzFTLUsJCmtxa8d8t4H.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s8",
      "text": "Folk tales have it that Emperor Huizong suffered from stomach pains after eating too much ice.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "民间传说宋徽宗在吃了太多的冰后感到胃痛。",
      "g": "主谓宾（宾语从句）",
      "d": "have it that... 有说法认为...；suffer from 遭受...之苦。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/K3yXPin2zg9oAxxQXWCetR.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s9",
      "text": "In the Yuan Dynasty, Marco Polo tasted binglao and carried the idea all the way back to Europe.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "在元朝，马可·波罗品尝了冰酪，并将这个创意一路带回了欧洲。",
      "g": "并列谓语",
      "d": "all the way 一路上。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/nRRi9akd6jDroqiJzd9UAY.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s10",
      "text": "People there added heavy cream and new tastes.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "那里的人们加入了厚奶油和新的口味。",
      "g": "主谓宾",
      "d": "add...to... 向...加入...。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/hdazSbuMKpP3RiZ7Fi6fG9.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s11",
      "text": "The rest is history!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p1",
      "tr": "剩下的就是历史了（众所周知了）！",
      "g": "固定表达",
      "d": "常用于描述某事发生后引发了一系列连锁反应。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/2bXhAQLrRv983J83pQCdqd.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s12",
      "text": "Sometimes, totally different cultures have similar dishes.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p2",
      "tr": "有时，完全不同的文化会有相似的菜肴。",
      "g": "主谓宾",
      "d": "similar 相似的。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/DrBnHYwm5M3M4XMnBxAr26.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s13",
      "text": "Iranians love a kind of flat bread, sangak.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p2",
      "tr": "伊朗人喜欢一种扁平的面包，叫作 sangak。",
      "g": "主谓宾 + 同位语",
      "d": "sangak 是 flat bread 的同位语。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/CmKB5jfZSHyB4DUELxoPd6.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s14",
      "text": "People in Shaanxi, China, love stone pancakes.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p2",
      "tr": "中国陕西的人们喜欢石子馍。",
      "g": "主谓宾",
      "d": "stone pancakes 对应中文的石子馍。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/gzeRQSQ6EBcP3iXG7S3kag.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s15",
      "text": "These two look almost the same!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p2",
      "tr": "这两者看起来几乎一模一样！",
      "g": "主系表",
      "d": "look the same 看起来一样。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/Uo2wbn8VeAYpApisJ7t3jA.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s16",
      "text": "People often compare roujiamo to hamburgers, a symbol of American food.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p2",
      "tr": "人们经常把肉夹馍比作汉堡，那是美国食物的象征。",
      "g": "主谓宾 + 宾补",
      "d": "compare A to B 把A比作B。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/gUrrGvLwq7Ry8qrGt7i4Tb.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s17",
      "text": "Many people call it the “Chinese hamburger”.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p2",
      "tr": "许多人称它为“中式汉堡”。",
      "g": "主谓宾宾补",
      "d": "call sth + name 称某物为...",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/ioFExZNJuXsDGHysYnfDGP.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s18",
      "text": "But in fact, arepas of Venezuela look more like the twin brother of roujiamo!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p2",
      "tr": "但事实上，委内瑞拉的 arepas 看起来更像是肉夹馍的孪生兄弟！",
      "g": "主系表",
      "d": "look like 看起来像。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/jKEh4ACcuB5ziT32QTjfRn.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s19",
      "text": "Food is a bridge between cultures.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p3",
      "tr": "食物是文化之间的桥梁。",
      "g": "主系表",
      "d": "bridge 桥梁，比喻沟通的媒介。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/q4svHcmNsTYsTXmmmC6GCV.mp3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-article-s20",
      "text": "When foods cross borders, sweet things can happen.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-article-p3",
      "tr": "当食物跨越国界时，美好的事情就会发生。",
      "g": "时间状语从句 + 主谓",
      "d": "cross borders 跨越国界。",
      "audioUrl": "https://musk-online.fbcontent.cn/pub-musk-ai-studio/workflow/file/audio/UvUFGUcAc2rbTr2Ywpxn8B.mp3"
    }
  ],
